        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 2 at 4:07PM CDT until June 2 at 5:00PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 407 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 4 miles northwest of Wayside to 13 miles east of Vigo
Park, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...70 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect some tree damage. Damage is likely to mobile homes,
roofs, and outbuildings. Hail damage to vehicles is
expected.

Locations impacted include...
Howardwick, Panhandle, Lake Mcclellan, Wayside, White Deer, Claude,
Groom, Clarendon, Greenbelt Lake, Goodnight, and Palo Duro Canyon.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
